assertor.title: QualWeb
assertor.description: QualWeb is an automatic accessibility evaluator for webpages.

test.title: Orientation of the page is not restricted using CSS transform property
test.description: This rule checks that page content is not restricted to either landscape or portrait orientation using CSS transform property.

result.description: A page where CSS transform property is applied to an element that is not visible.

test.title: Meta-refresh no delay
test.description: This rule checks that the meta element is not used for delayed redirecting or refreshing.

result.description: Inexistent attribute "content"

test.title: Image button has accessible name
test.description: This rule checks that each image button element has an accessible name.

result.description: There isn't an image button to test

test.title: svg element with explicit role has accessible name
test.description: This rule checks that each SVG image element that is explicitly included in the accessibility tree has an accessible name.

result.description: No svg elements

test.title: Element within body has valid lang attribute
test.description: This rule checks that the lang attribute of an element in the page body has a valid primary language subtag.

result.description: No elements with lang

test.title: meta viewport does not prevent zoom
test.description: This rule checks that the meta element retains the user agent ability to zoom.

result.description: The meta name="viewport" element does not define the maximum-scale and user-scalable values.

test.title: HTML Page has a title
test.description: This rule checks that the HTML page has a title.

result.pointer: html > head > title:nth-of-type(1)

result.description: Title element exists and it's not empty

test.title: Validity of HTML Lang attribute
test.description: This rule checks the lang or xml:lang attribute has a valid language subtag.

result.pointer: html

result.description: The lang attribute has a valid value

test.title: `id` attribute value is unique
test.description: This rule checks that all id attribute values on a single page are unique.
